rComments: He's a good teacher. This class is fairly hard. He dosen't give gifts on the exams/finals but I beleive that it's just because the content is genuinely challenging. Overall, no issues with this prof, he'll answer questions after class and help you 1-1 if needed.

Tough Mid term with a lot of questions (he clearly tells you that you wont have enough time to finish it so you must sacrifice points of your grades) and Quiz (the textbook exercises does not have any similarity with his quiz). You get told to read the textbook but the difficulty of the textbook exercises is too simple compared with his exams.

You don't need the teacher as there are no courses on brightspace, you pay the course to get told to read the book. The professor is sympathetic but the course contains nothing, you need to teach yourself.

The class seems difficult at first, but you have to put in the effort. His teaching wasn't AMAZING, but I liked that he gave examples from his real-world experience to try and make things more understandable. Biggest tip for this class: practice! practice! practice! And make a list questions on hard concepts to ask them later.
Doesn't respond to emails, tough mid term
